title: Kimball tops Burns for 10th win of season
text:
Kimball tops Burns for 10th win of season Star-Herald Staff Report Star Herald 
BURNS, Wyo. â€” The Kimball volleyball team registered its 10th win of the season by sweeping Burns, Wyoming, 25-14, 25-18, 25-17 on Thursday. 
Madison Biesecker led the Longhorns with a triple-double of 12 points, 10 kills and 18 set assists. Danika Daum finished with a double-double of 15 kills and 12 assists. She also led Kimball with seven blocks. Madie Snyder served a team-high 15 points. Ali Hunsaker added 14 points. Raelynn Hinton chipped in with eight kills.
